<h1 class="jazz-page-title">Breadcrumbs</h1>

<p>
Breadcrumbs are a hierarchical list of links that indicate where the current page is situated within the overall information architecture.
</p>

<p>
Each link in the Breadcrumbs provides quick navigation to related pages in the site hierarchy.
</p>

{{ example("/components/breadcrumbs/breadcrumbs-example1", "Demonstration", "code-panel-demo") }}

<h2>Best Practices</h2>

<ul>
    <li>Help users understand where they are within a site/application.</li>
    <li>Link labels used in the Breadcrumbs should match the page titles used on the corresponding pages.</li>
    <li>Strive to keep site hierarchies shallow to avoid burying content deep in the information architecture.  This will result in long Breadcrumb trails.</li>
    <li>Evaluate if Breadcrumbs are even necessary for pages where the hierarchy is very shallow or the site hierarchy is already clearly represented in the existing navigation structure.</li>
    <li>Breadcrumbs should not be used to manage a workflow.  Other patterns, such as “wizards” or “steppers” would be more appropriate for that use case.</li>
    <li>Do not represent a site hierarchy where one does not exist.</li>
    <li>Breadcrumbs are not a replacement for native browser “Back” button navigation.  Wherever possible, do not disable native browser “Back” button navigation.</li>
    <li>Add JSON-LD (<a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/data-types/breadcrumb">https://developers.google.com/search/docs/data-types/breadcrumb</a>) as a search engine optimization where it is useful.</li>
    <li>Use only a single set of Breadcrumbs on a page.</li>
</ul>

