<h2>Detailed Specification</h2>

<h3>Design</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Breadcrumbs are made up of Breadcrumb Items separated by the Breadcrumb Separator.</li>
    <li>Each Breadcrumb Item is a link that can be made up of a text label and an optional icon.</li>
    <li>The current page is represented as plain text, not an active link.</li>
    <li>Icons are always shown to the left of the label.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Code</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Breadcrumbs are wrapped in a <span class="code">nav</span> element to indicate their purpose.</li>
    <li>The <span class="code">nav</span> element is given an <span class="code">aria-label</span> of “Breadcrumbs” for use by assistive technologies.</li>
    <li>The list of links is implemented as a simple order list (<span class="code">ol</span>).</li>
    <li>The current page is indicated by adding the <span class="code">aria-current=’page’</span> attribute to the appropriate <span class="code">li</span>.</li>
    <li>The forward slash (“/”) is used as a separator between items in the Breadcrumb list. </li>
    <li>The last Breadcrumb item represents the current page and should not be an active link.</li>
    <li>Breadcrumbs will never wrap.</li>
    <li>The Breadcrumbs will be truncated (with ellipsis: “...”) when the Breadcrumbs are too wide to fit on the screen.</li>
    <li>Breadcrumb labels will never wrap.</li>
    <li>If icons are used as part of the label, they should always be on the left side of the label and should never be used alone.</li>
</ul>

<h3>States</h3>

<h4>Default</h4>
<p>The Default state of a breadcrumb item will be Not Current.</p>
<h4>Active</h4>
<p>The breadcrumb item is in the process of being selected.</p>
<h4>Not Current</h4>
<p>The breadcrumb item represents a location (page) that is not the current location (page).  The breadcrumb item is represented as a link.</p>
<h4>Current</h4>
<p>The breadcrumb item represents the current location (page).  The breadcrumb item is represented as plain text that is not a link, and will not obtain focus.</p>
<h4>Focus</h4>
<p>The breadcrumb item has focus.</p>
<h4>Hover</h4>
<p>The mouse cursor is within the breadcrumb item.</p>
<h4>Overflow</h4>
<p>The breadcrumb items do not fit within the available horizontal space.</p>


